// Man page for hex
manHex="HEX(1)                           X Shell Manual                           HEX(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    hex - hexadecimal calculator with arithmetic and bitwise operations
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>hex VALUE</b>
    <b>hex VALUE OPERATOR VALUE2</b>
    <b>command | hex [OPERATOR VALUE2]</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Perform arithmetic or bitwise operations on hex or decimal values.
    Input accepts 0x-prefixed hex (e.g. 0x2A99789D) or plain decimal.
    Output is always shown as 0xRESULT (decimal N).

    Useful for working with exploit memory addresses from mtree.
<b>OPERATORS</b>
    <b>+</b>        Addition
    <b>-</b>        Subtraction
    <b>*</b>        Multiplication
    <b>/</b>        Integer division
    <b>-and</b>     Bitwise AND
    <b>-or</b>      Bitwise OR
    <b>-xor</b>     Bitwise XOR
    <b>-ls</b>      Left shift
    <b>-rs</b>      Right shift
<b>EXAMPLES</b>
    <b>hex 0x2A99789D</b>
    Display hex value with decimal equivalent.

    <b>hex 0x2A99789D + 0x100</b>
    Add 0x100 to a memory address.

    <b>hex 0x2A99789D - 715553949</b>
    Subtract a decimal value from a hex address.

    <b>hex 0xFF -and 0x0F</b>
    Bitwise AND — result: 0xF (decimal: 15)

    <b>hex 0x1 -ls 8</b>
    Left shift — result: 0x100 (decimal: 256)

    <b>hex 715553949</b>
    Show decimal as hex: 0x2A99789D (decimal: 715553949)

    <b>cat mtree | hex + 0x100</b>
    Add 0x100 offset to every address in an mtree file."